  "description": "Karl Georg Eliasson was a Swedish chief engineer born in Halmstad to builder Jöns E. and Christina Andersson on July 14, 1884. He graduated from Halmstad's high school in 1906 and went on to attend CTL (E) and the Technische Hochschule in Karlsruhe from 1906 to 1907. From 1912 to 1939 he traveled to various countries including Germany, Switzerland, Italy, Austria, France, Denmark, Norway, and Finland. Karl worked as an engineer and consultant for various organizations including Luth & Roséns Elektr. A-B, CTI, and his own electrical engineering consulting firm and laboratory. His clients included the power plants in Varberg, Lysekil, Kungälv, Kungsbacka, Mölndal, and Mellerud. He was also a member and held various positions in organizations such as the Swedish Institute of Engineering, the Odd Fellow, Par Bricole, and Bachelor's Club. Karl Georg Eliasson had hobbies such as shooting and amateur film-making and was the recipient of RNO, RVO, RFinlLO, ProPatrstGM, Patrst-GM honors."
